Py-test dot raises — testing for exceptions.

When a function is supposed to raise an exception, py-test dot raises captures it as a context manager.

The pattern. Import py-test. Def parse-age takes a string, ints it, raises value-error if negative, otherwise returns. Def test-negative-age-rejected uses with py-test dot raises of value-error, match equals non-negative, then calls parse-age of negative five.

Match accepts a regular expression against the exception's string. The with block must raise an exception of the expected type, or the test fails.

In code, picture exactly that test. Wrap the negative call in a with-raises and confirm it works. Then wrap a non-failing call in with-raises — that test fails because no exception was raised.
